The paper discusses Qualitative Spatial and Temporal Reasoning (QSTR), which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (AI) concerned with symbolic knowledge representation. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the algebraic properties of the qualitative calculi, which suggests that it may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses computational properties, which could place it in the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) or Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses spatial and temporal reasoning, which could place it in the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
